HEADWORD: Cardigan jacket
<hw>Car"di*gan jack`et</hw></mhw>
<pr>(#)</pr>. <ety>[From the Earl of <etsep>Cardigan</etsep>, who was
famous in the Crimean campaign of 1854-55.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
warm jacket of knit worsted with or without sleeves, especially a
knitted jacket with sleeves that is fastened up the front with buttons
or a zipper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cardigan</ent>⟦br⟧
